CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 18, 1961, pg. 24, reads: "Up Calloway's Back? - The frenzied action of victorious City Basketball League championship-winning Fifth Avenue High School is captured in above, as the "Archer's" Fleming Reynolds (40) appears to be climbing the back of Ulna Calloway (31), South Hil's [sic] scoring ace, to notch one of the goals that contributed to an upset, 57-51 victory for the charges of Coach George Cupples. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Fifth Avenue High School basketball player #40 Fleming Reynolds leaping over South Hills basketball player #31 Ulna Calloway, to shoot ball, in arena
